@Maintenance of foraging trails by the giant tropical ant Paraponera clavata (Insecta: Formicidae: Ponerinae)

{{paper bioant/fulltext-10.pdf}}
<http://www.springerlink.com/content/j868p830ur8776w8/>

C. R. Nelson1, C. D. Jorgensen2, H. L. Black2 and J. Whiting2
{{category C. R. Nelson}}
{{category C. D. Jorgensen}}
{{category H. L. Black}}
{{category J. Whiting}}

(1) 	Brackenridge Field Laboratory and Department of Zoology, University of Texas, 78712 Austin, TX
(2) 	Department of Zoology, Brigham Young University, 84602 Provo, UT

Received: 14 June 1990  Revised: 5 October 1990  Accepted: 19 November 1990  
{{category 1990}}

*Summary

Establishment and maintenance of foraging trails to an artificial nectar source by ten colonies ofParaponera davata (Fabr.) in Panama is reported. The first forager to locate the artificial nectar source was responsible for recruiting additional foragers and for marking trails to orient these foragers. More than half of the trail marking was performed by the first two ants to mark the path back to the colony, although up to 11 ants per colony per hour marked trails. The number of trail marks and the number of marking ants decreased through time, presumably as foragers learned the location of the artificial nectar source. Four categories of recruits were noted: markers, foragers, patrollers, and visitors.

Key words  Recruitment - trail marking - pheromone trails - trail maintenance - patrolling

{{category 生物のアリ}}
{{category アリの採餌行動}}

*要旨

- 最初に餌をみつけたアリが巣に戻り、他のアリに知らせる。
- 知らされたアリは (分岐があるにもかかわらず) まっすぐ餌に向かう。
- 最初のアリは分岐点で立ち止まることがある。
- 知らされたアリが餌を持って戻ると、更に別のアリに知らせる。
- 最初に餌をみつけたアリほどよくフェロモンを置く。半分近くが最初の1匹によるフェロモン。
- どのアリもだんだんフェロモンを置くことは減っていく。
- アリは4種類に分けられる
-- 餌を運ぶ。フェロモンを置く。
-- 餌を運ぶ。フェロモンは置かない。これが一番多い。
-- 餌や経路付近を「パトロール」する。
-- 餌まで行くが何も持たずに帰る。

